THE KZN State of the Province Address was delivered for the first time in the presence of hopeful Zulu King Misizulu kaZwelithini. The event was held at the Royal Show Grounds in Pietermaritzburg on Thursday, 24 February. When King Misuzulu entered the venue, KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala was forced to pause his speech as he was a few minutes late. He was accompanied by chanting Amabutho and his praise singer ushered him to the chair delivered to the venue beforehand. Continuing, Zikalala said the province had to deal with both Covid-19 and the July unrest. ALSO READ | PICS: ‘WORLD MUST STOP PUTIN!’ “We must set our compass to conquer the high seas of job creation, economic recovery, the fight against crime, water provision, building a capable and incorruptible government,” said Zikalala. He said the unemployment rate had risen to 28,7% from 23%. “We need major economic reforms anchored on radical economic transformation and greater participation in the mainstream economy.” ALSO READ | MUTHI WAR OF WIFE AND NYATSI BLOCKS HUSBAND’S 4-5! EFF chairman Vusi Khoza said Zikalala failed to instil confidence. “There was nothing new in his speech. It was the same things he promised last year,” said Khoza.